---
import Landing from '../../layouts/Landing.astro';
---

<Landing
	title="Blog — mcp-flowgate"
	description="Updates, guides, and deep dives from the mcp-flowgate project."
>

<nav class="fixed top-0 w-full z-50 backdrop-blur-md bg-slate-950/80 border-b border-slate-800">
	<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 h-16 flex items-center justify-between">
		<a href="/" class="text-white font-semibold text-lg">mcp-flowgate</a>
		<div class="flex items-center gap-8">
			<a href="/introduction" class="text-slate-300 hover:text-white text-sm transition-colors">Docs</a>
			<a href="/examples" class="text-slate-300 hover:text-white text-sm transition-colors">Examples</a>
			<a href="/blog" class="text-white text-sm font-medium">Blog</a>
			<a href="https://github.com/matt-cochran/mcp-flowgate" class="text-slate-300 hover:text-white text-sm transition-colors">GitHub</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</nav>

<section class="pt-32 pb-20 px-6 bg-white min-h-screen">
	<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
		<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Blog</h1>
		<p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-12">
			Project updates, technical deep dives, and things we learned building mcp-flowgate.
		</p>

		<!-- Welcome -->
		<article class="blog-card mb-8">
			<a href="/blog/welcome" class="block">
				<time class="text-sm text-slate-400" datetime="2026-04-02">April 2, 2026</time>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-1 mb-2 hover:text-indigo-600 transition-colors">
					The bet behind mcp-flowgate
				</h2>
				<p class="text-slate-600">
					Your model reads every tool you register on every call, and
					none of it comes with governance. Here's the one bet
					mcp-flowgate makes to fix both — and an honest account of
					what's built so far.
				</p>
			</a>
		</article>

		<!-- Not just for coding -->
		<article class="blog-card mb-8">
			<a href="/blog/not-just-for-coding" class="block">
				<time class="text-sm text-slate-400" datetime="2026-04-09">April 9, 2026</time>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-1 mb-2 hover:text-indigo-600 transition-colors">
					What do a deploy pipeline and an expense report have in common?
				</h2>
				<p class="text-slate-600">
					mcp-flowgate is not an agentic coding tool. Coding is one
					use case among many — and new regulation is fast making the
					audit trail it produces a requirement.
				</p>
			</a>
		</article>

		<!-- Hidden cost -->
		<article class="blog-card mb-8">
			<a href="/blog/hidden-cost-of-mcp-tools" class="block">
				<time class="text-sm text-slate-400" datetime="2026-04-14">April 14, 2026</time>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-1 mb-2 hover:text-indigo-600 transition-colors">
					The hidden cost of 50 MCP tools
				</h2>
				<p class="text-slate-600">
					Every tool you register is a recurring tax: input tokens for
					its definition, output tokens for the reasoning to choose
					it. Here's the math, measured.
				</p>
			</a>
		</article>

		<!-- State machines -->
		<article class="blog-card mb-8">
			<a href="/blog/why-agents-need-state-machines" class="block">
				<time class="text-sm text-slate-400" datetime="2026-04-16">April 16, 2026</time>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-1 mb-2 hover:text-indigo-600 transition-colors">
					Why your AI agent needs a state machine
				</h2>
				<p class="text-slate-600">
					When an agent acts out of order, the fix isn't a longer
					prompt. It's the oldest, most boring pattern in computing —
					and agent governance is exactly the problem it was built for.
				</p>
			</a>
		</article>

		<!-- HATEOAS -->
		<article class="blog-card mb-8">
			<a href="/blog/hateoas-for-ai" class="block">
				<time class="text-sm text-slate-400" datetime="2026-04-21">April 21, 2026</time>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-1 mb-2 hover:text-indigo-600 transition-colors">
					HATEOAS for AI: REST's oldest idea is the right pattern for agents
				</h2>
				<p class="text-slate-600">
					An LLM is a client that's bad at remembering rules. So stop
					making it. Let every response carry the legal next moves.
				</p>
			</a>
		</article>

		<!-- Governance -->
		<article class="blog-card mb-8">
			<a href="/blog/governance-is-not-application-code" class="block">
				<time class="text-sm text-slate-400" datetime="2026-04-23">April 23, 2026</time>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-1 mb-2 hover:text-indigo-600 transition-colors">
					Stop writing approval gates in code
				</h2>
				<p class="text-slate-600">
					Approval gates and permission checks written inside each
					tool drift, can't be reviewed as a set, and are invisible.
					Declare them as data instead.
				</p>
			</a>
		</article>

		<!-- Flat tool lists -->
		<article class="blog-card mb-8">
			<a href="/blog/flat-tool-lists-dont-scale" class="block">
				<time class="text-sm text-slate-400" datetime="2026-04-30">April 30, 2026</time>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-1 mb-2 hover:text-indigo-600 transition-colors">
					Flat tool lists don't scale — and agents are about to find out
				</h2>
				<p class="text-slate-600">
					A flat tool list is fine at 12 tools and quietly breaks at
					200. The failure isn't only tokens — it's that the model has
					no structure to navigate.
				</p>
			</a>
		</article>

		<!-- MCP security -->
		<article class="blog-card mb-8">
			<a href="/blog/mcp-security-gateway-layer" class="block">
				<time class="text-sm text-slate-400" datetime="2026-05-07">May 7, 2026</time>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-1 mb-2 hover:text-indigo-600 transition-colors">
					Where MCP security actually lives — and where it doesn't yet
				</h2>
				<p class="text-slate-600">
					The security controls that don't fit in a tool definition
					need a layer of their own. Here's what a gateway enforces —
					and an honest account of what it doesn't.
				</p>
			</a>
		</article>

		<!-- Generator not a calculator -->
		<article class="blog-card mb-8">
			<a href="/blog/generator-not-a-calculator" class="block">
				<time class="text-sm text-slate-400" datetime="2026-05-19">May 19, 2026</time>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-1 mb-2 hover:text-indigo-600 transition-colors">
					Your LLM is a generator, not a calculator
				</h2>
				<p class="text-slate-600">
					An LLM does one kind of work: generation. It can't compute —
					by design, not by immaturity. Match each job to the tool
					built for it, and both shine.
				</p>
			</a>
		</article>

		<!-- Deterministic chaining -->
		<article class="blog-card mb-8">
			<a href="/blog/deterministic-chaining" class="block">
				<time class="text-sm text-slate-400" datetime="2026-05-21">May 21, 2026</time>
				<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-1 mb-2 hover:text-indigo-600 transition-colors">
					Deterministic chaining: when you don't need the LLM to decide
				</h2>
				<p class="text-slate-600">
					Not every pipeline step is a decision. Tag the computable
					ones and the runtime runs them itself — the model only wakes
					for the choices that matter.
				</p>
			</a>
		</article>

	</div>
</section>

<footer class="py-12 px-6 bg-slate-950 border-t border-slate-800">
	<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto flex flex-wrap justify-between items-start gap-8">
		<div>
			<p class="text-white font-semibold mb-2">mcp-flowgate</p>
			<p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Composable MCP control layer.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="flex gap-12">
			<div>
				<p class="text-slate-400 font-medium text-sm mb-2">Resources</p>
				<ul class="space-y-1">
					<li><a href="/introduction" class="text-slate-500 hover:text-slate-300 text-sm">Docs</a></li>
					<li><a href="/examples" class="text-slate-500 hover:text-slate-300 text-sm">Examples</a></li>
					<li><a href="/blog" class="text-slate-500 hover:text-slate-300 text-sm">Blog</a></li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div>
				<p class="text-slate-400 font-medium text-sm mb-2">Community</p>
				<ul class="space-y-1">
					<li><a href="https://github.com/matt-cochran/mcp-flowgate" class="text-slate-500 hover:text-slate-300 text-sm">GitHub</a></li>
					<li><a href="https://github.com/matt-cochran/mcp-flowgate/issues" class="text-slate-500 hover:text-slate-300 text-sm">Issues</a></li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</footer>

</Landing>
